    "title": "Applying biquadratic filters to a music loop"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can shape the output of an audio signal, such as by boosting or cutting the bass or treble of a music track, with the single-channel and multichannel biquadratic filters that the vDSP library provides.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The vDSP library defines a biquadratic filter from a set of five coefficients for each section. This sample code app calculates those coefficients from a set of properties that it displays as controls in the user interface. The user interface provides controls to select the filter type (such as low-pass or high-pass), the center frequency of the filter, and the Q value that controls the width of the filter’s frequency band.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The sample code app displays the magnitude response of the selected section, the magnitude response of the entire filter, the frequency-domain representation of the input signal, and the frequency-domain representation of the filtered, output signal.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "biquad-demo-overview.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Before exploring the code, try building and running the app to familiarize yourself with the effect of the different parameters on the music loop.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Initialize-the-biquadratic-filter",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Initialize the biquadratic filter",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "biquadSectionCount",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " constant defines the number of sections that the biquadratic filter implements. The sample code app sets this to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "3",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " by default.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "public let biquadSectionCount = vDSP_Length(3)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.accelerate/documentation/Accelerate/vDSP_biquad_CreateSetup",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function returns a new biquadratic filter structure that contains ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "biquadSectionCount",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " sections. The sample code app defines the coefficients to produce a filter that returns an output that’s identical to the input.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "let coefficients = [[Float]](",
            "    repeating: BiquadCoefficientCalculator.passthroughCoefficients.array,",
            "    count: Int(biquadSectionCount)).flatMap {",
            "        $0",
            "}",
            "",
            "biquadSetup = vDSP_biquad_CreateSetup(vDSP.floatToDouble(coefficients),",
            "                                      biquadSectionCount)!"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Define-the-biquadratic-coefficients",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Define the biquadratic coefficients",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Five coefficients define each section of a biquadratic filter. The following formula describes the underlying math of the biquadratic filter, with ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "z",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text": " referring to the complex frequency-domain representation of the signal:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "biquad_formula.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The sample code app includes the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "BiquadCoefficientCalculator",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " structure that provides the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "static BiquadCoefficientCalculator.coefficients(for:sampleRate:)",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function. This function returns the five coefficients for a filter type, center frequency, Q, and sample rate.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Each filter type uses the same shared values.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "let omega = 2.0 * .pi * frequency / Float(sampleRate)",
            "let sinOmega = sin(omega)",
            "let alpha = sinOmega / (2 * Q)",
            "let cosOmega = cos(omega)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "switch",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " statement calculates the coefficients for each filter type case. For example, the following code calculates the coefficients for a low-pass filter (that reduces high frequencies):",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "case .lowpass:",
            "    b0 = (1 - cosOmega) / 2",
            "    b1 = 1 - cosOmega",
            "    b2 = (1 - cosOmega) / 2",
            "    a0 = 1 + alpha",
            "    a1 = -2 * cosOmega",
            "    a2 = 1 - alpha"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Set-the-biquadratic-coefficients",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Set the biquadratic coefficients",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.accelerate/documentation/Accelerate/vDSP_biquad_SetCoefficientsSingle",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function sets the coefficients for a section of the biquadratic filter. The sample code app defines ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "selectedSectionIndex",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " as the index of the currently selected section, and the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "BiquadCoefficientCalculator.SectionCoefficients",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " structure provides an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "array",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " variable that returns ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "[b0, b1, b2, a1, a2]",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "vDSP_biquad_SetCoefficientsSingle(biquadSetup,",
            "                                  selectedSectionCoefficients.array,",
            "                                  vDSP_Length(selectedSectionIndex),",
            "                                  1)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Apply-the-biquadratic-filter-to-the-audio-sample",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Apply the biquadratic filter to the audio sample",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.accelerate/documentation/Accelerate/vDSP_biquad",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function applies the biquadratic filter to a page of input samples and writes the result to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "outputSignal",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " array. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "delay",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " array contains the past state for each section of the biquadratic filter.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "vDSP_biquad(biquadSetup,",
            "            &delay,",
            "            page, 1,",
            "            &outputSignal, 1,",
            "            vDSP_Length(Self.sampleCount))"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "On return, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "outputSignal",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " contains the filtered version of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "page",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "delay",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " contains the final state data of the filter. The sample code app passes ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "delay",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to the next call of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.accelerate/documentation/Accelerate/vDSP_biquad",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
